                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13209107" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 16 Feb 2012 04:19:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch with the general idea of what I am thinking - we store the orig solr.xml dom structure as a field. We also store a mapping from SolrCore to orginal core name. We have to keep that up to date on core reload. Then when writing out the solr.xml file we can use both those data structures to see if we should use the original raw value, a new updated value, etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13209498" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 16 Feb 2012 16:54:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updates patch - close to done I think - I don&apos;t handle &amp;lt;properties because of some oddity I have not figured out - they appear to stored un-sys-subbed, but then when written out they are subbed? I&apos;m not sure they are that important to handle anyway?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13211026" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sat, 18 Feb 2012 17:34:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still a small issue here - in reload we try to maintain the link of a SolrCore-&amp;gt;orig solr.xml name mapping - but if the core was dynamically created, the orig name will be null and so we must check for that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13215892" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 24 Feb 2012 20:47:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a bug here where you might lose some core attribs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
